  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\nSpecifying a specific private key file is too hard with teku.  A couple of improvements we should make:\n\n - Automatically trim whitespace from the file before trying to parse as hex (currently it fails if there's a newline in the key file)\n - Change the `teku peer generate` subcommand to be more directly useful.  It should write the private key to a file in the format required to be used with `--p2p-private-key-file` and just print the public key and peerId to the console.  It should always generate a single key rather than multiple and have a more sensible default output file (probably just private-key.txt).",
