    "body": "Some clarification.\r\n\r\nWith space/new-line in the end of the hex string this error is displayed:\r\n```\r\nTeku failed to start: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Invalid odd-length hex binary representation\r\n```\r\nWith incorrect key length:\r\n```\r\nTeku failed to start: com.google.protobuf.InvalidProtocolBufferException: While parsing a protocol message, the input ended unexpectedly in the middle of a field.  This could mean either that the input has been truncated or that an embedded message misreported its own length.\r\n```\r\nBoth errors give no information to the user. It's even not clear it's linked to the peer key",
